The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Mexican Colony had a population of 283. The population density was {{convert|8,843.8|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Mexican Colony was 62 (21.9%) [[White Americans|White]], 1 (0.4%) [[African Americans|African American]], 16 (5.7%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 2 (0.7%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 152 (53.7%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 50 (17.7%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 261 persons (92.2%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Mexican Colony CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0647192 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 29, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 72 households, out of which 37 (51.4%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 34 (47.2%) were married-couple households, 12 (16.7%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 6 (8.3%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 20 (27.8%) had a male householder with no partner present. 15 households (20.8%) were one person, and 4 (5.6%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 3.93.<ref name=DP1/> There were 52 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (72.2% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Mexican Colony CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0647192 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 29, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 107 people (37.8%) under the age of 18, 38 people (13.4%) aged 18 to 24, 55 people (19.4%) aged 25 to 44, 62 people (21.9%) aged 45 to 64, and 21 people (7.4%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 23.6{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 122.8 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 73 housing units at an average density of {{convert|2,281.2|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 72 (98.6%) were occupied. Of these, 17 (23.6%) were owner-occupied, and 55 (76.4%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

